job_description: Software Engineer 3 (contract) - job post Boeing 9,061 reviews El Segundo, CA 90245 Contract Boeing 9,061 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. You must create an Indeed account before continuing to the company website to apply Apply on company site save-icon Job details Job Type Contract Boeing Defense, Space & Security (BDS) is seeking Senior Mission Processing Software Engineers for their Satellite Systems Division located in Seal Beach, CA, El Segundo, CA, or Mesa, AZ. We are seeking engineers that are passionate about space and motivated to be part of a multi-disciplined, collaborative engineering environment that supports the design, development, and implementation of software for Boeing built government space products! This is an opportunity to work in a rapid development environment using modern technology, architecture, and tools. We need your help to develop software capabilities for mission data processing of sensor raw data to provide operational products to the customer. Our team works within an agile methodology using a CI/CD environment; integrated with automated testing, vulnerability, & quality scanning capabilities. The software team uses the Python language and leverages artificial intelligence / machine learning concepts. You will directly partner with customer counterparts and program management to deliver the highest value capabilities, performing demonstrations along the way. The role requires a creativity and you will be encouraged to automate manual processes and workflows where possible. The candidate should possess excellent communications skills and work well in a team environment to support the needs of the Integrated Product Team. This senior position requires proven experience within the software ecosystem, a unique background of project experience, and the clear exhibition of superior judgment and decision making to engineer new solutions and capabilities. Critical thinking and troubleshooting skills are required! Primary Responsibilities & Expectations: Refactoring legacy application into a new cloud-based framework and provide enhancements to existing capabilities. Develop and maintain requirements, architectures, algorithms, interfaces, and designs for new product capabilities. Perform software development in the agile methodology utilizing a DevSecOps environment where you will support continuous team improvement. Build software test procedures and environments, implement the tests and document results to ensure software system requirements are met. Present progress demonstrations to customer representatives and satellite program leadership. Boeing is the world's largest aerospace company and leading manufacturer of commercial airplanes and defense, space and security systems. We are engineers and technicians. Skilled scientists and problem solvers. Bold innovators and dreamers. Join us, and you can build something better for yourself, for our customers and for the world. This position is expected to be 100% onsite. The selected candidate will be required to work onsite at one of the listed location options. This position requires an active U.S. Top Secret Security/SCI Clearance (U.S. Citizenship Required). (A U.S. Security Clearance that has been active in the past 24 months is considered active). This position requires a current Tier 5 (T5), formerly known as a Single Scope Background Investigation (SSBI) (U.S. Citizenship required) with current polygraph. Basic Qualifications (Required Skills/Experience): Bachelor’s, Master’s or Doctorate degree from an accredited course of study, in Computer Engineering, Software Engineering, Computer Science or another related field. 5 or more years of experience with the Python software language. Software development experience in a collaborative team environment using agile principles and a structured development process including code reviews and DevOps processes/tools. Experience using team collaboration tools including Git, JIRA, Confluence, Artifactory, etc. Preferred Qualifications (Desired Skills/Experience): Experience with artificial intelligence and machine learning concepts. Experience with sensor process and image formation. Current CompTIA Security+ certification. Experience using SonarQube and/or Coverity to manage code quality. Experience with cloud computing and virtualization technologies and containerized applications and frameworks (Jupyter, Docker, Kubernetes, Helm). Experience with Python numerical tools (numpy, scipy), GIS tools for python & map front-ends (OpenLayers/Cesium). Typical Education/Experience: Bachelor's degree and typically 9 or more years' experience in an engineering classification or a Master's degree with typically 7 or more years' experience in an engineering classification or a PhD degree with typically 4 or more years' experience in an engineering classification. Bachelor, Master or Doctorate of Science degree from an accredited course of study, in engineering, computer science, mathematics, physics or chemistry. ABET is the preferred, although not required, accreditation standard.

You must create an Indeed account before continuing to the company website to apply Apply on company site save-icon Job details Job Type Contract Duration: 5+ Months Job description: Responsibilities: Design and develop functional test equipment for printed circuit board assemblies (PCBAs). Troubleshooting DC fast charger PCBAs and units to determine root cause and support design engineers with the development of corrective actions. Define automation needs and work with automation engineers to improve end-of-line throughput. Assisting system and validation teams with setup and executing various certification tests onsite and offsite. Document test equipment designs via electrical wiring schematics. Work closely with the engineering project teams to ensure test equipment designs align with the software and hardware requirements. Participate in design reviews, requirement reviews, DFMEAs, PFMEAs, and Hazard Analyses. Develop test procedures defining specific test setup requirements and instructions. Perform data analysis and generate reports. Utilize standard electronic test equipment such as power supplies, oscilloscopes, multimeters, signal generators, and power analyzers. Use sensors such as thermocouples, RTDs, current, and voltage. Core Responsibilities: B.S. in Electrical/Electronic Engineering, Computer Science, or a related field. 2+ years experience designing circuit board assembly functional test equipment. 2+ years experience designing test equipment for high voltage power electronics. Ability to create schematics using design software tools such as OrCAD, and AutoCAD Electrical. Familiarity with modular test instruments and National Instruments I/O Systems (PXI, cDAQ) Knowledge of and experience with computer hardware, communication, and bus protocols (RS232, CAN, GPIB, Ethernet, USB). Hands-on experience with diagnosing and troubleshooting complex issues Ability to work in a fast-paced development environment Programming ability such as LabVIEW is a plus. PCB design experience is a plus Comments for Suppliers: Looking for an electrical test engineer to concentrate on designing and setting up test stations for PCBAs. This candidate will be mostly working on the DC fast charger program and will be testing and troubleshooting PCBAs and components of the charger. This is mainly for prototype end-of-line testing (lower volume) Test Engineer must have: Experience with high voltage power, Oscilloscopes, power analyzers, and basic experience with automation systems to be able to work with the LabVIEW engineer. Experience creating test procedures and reports, performing data analysis, and electrical design using CAD software such as AutoCAD electrical. Experience troubleshooting electrical test setups There could be up to 20% of travel (probably less). This could be local or out of state. Experience with National Instrument hardware is desired.
